Definition of Stock() Class¶

*Attributes for the class:*

  • ticker
  • start_date
  • end_date
  • equity (default value is 1000000)

*Method of this class should be:*

  • 1. CurPrice(curDate) Which gives the closing price of the date curDate.

  • 2. NDayRet(N,curDate) Which gives the N-day returns as on the curDate. (N=5 will give 5-day return)

  • 3. DailyRet(curDate) - Which gives the daily returns on curDate.

  • 4. Last30daysPrice(curDate) Which gives the array of last 30 days prices.

In [16]:
class Stock:
    
    def __init__(self, ticker, start_date, end_date, equity=1000000):
        self.ticker = ticker
        self.start_date = start_date
        self.end_date = end_date
        self.equity = equity
        self.stock_info_df = self.price_history_dataframe()
        
        
    def price_history_dataframe(self):
        start_date = self.start_date
        end_date = self.end_date
        try:
            ticker = self.ticker # +'.NS'
            data = yf.download(ticker, start=start_date, end=end_date) 
            return data        
        except Exception as e:
            return f'ERROR in downloading: {e}'           
    
        
    def CurPrice(self, curDate):
        '''returns the closing price for the curDate'''
        try:
            closing_price  = self.stock_info_df['Close'] 
            return f'Closing price on {curDate}: {closing_price.loc[curDate]}'         
        except:
            return f'Maybe market is closed...try for next date'
        
    
    def NDayRet(self, N, curDate):
        '''returns the N-day returns as on the curDate. (N=5 will give 5-day return)'''
        try:
            adj_close = self.stock_info_df['Adj Close']
            NdayReturn = adj_close.pct_change(N)
            return f'Return for last {N} day on {curDate}: {NdayReturn[curDate]}'        
        except:
             return f'Try for different N or date value'   

    
    def DailyRet(self, curDate):
        '''gives the daily returns on curDate.'''
        adj_close = self.stock_info_df['Adj Close'] 
        daily_return = adj_close.pct_change(1)
        return f'Daily return for {curDate} is: {daily_return[curDate]}' 
    
    
    def Last30daysPrice(self, curDate):
        '''returns the array of last 30 days prices'''
        closing_price  = self.stock_info_df['Close'] 
        min_idx = min(closing_price.index)
        max_idx =  curDate        
        try:        
            if len(closing_price[min_idx : max_idx]) <=30:
                return np.array(closing_price[min_idx : max_idx])
            else:
                max_idx = datetime.strptime(max_idx, '%Y-%m-%d')
                min_idx = max_idx - dt.timedelta(days=30)
                return np.array(closing_price[min_idx : max_idx])        
        except:
            return f'Try for different N or date value'

1. Benchmark Strategy:¶

Our Benchmark is going to be Nifty50 index itself. Compare your active stock selection strategy.

2. Active stock selection strategy:¶

Your task involves creating an investment strategy where, at the end of each month, the performance of each stock in the previous month is assessed. The criterion for selection is positive returns. For instance, on March 31st of a given year, the 30-day returns of all fifty stocks will be examined, and only those with positive returns will be included in the portfolio. This portfolio will be maintained until April 30th, when a revaluation will occur based on the same rule for the upcoming month. This process will be repeated monthly

def get_n50_dataframe():
    dataframe_list = []
    
    for item in n50_list:
        globals()[item] = Stock(ticker=item+'.NS', start_date=start_date, end_date=end_date)
        dataframe_list.append((item, globals()[item])) 
        
    return dataframe_list

def modified_dataframe_list():
    arr = []
    for item, value in n50_dataframe_list:
        item = value.stock_info_df
        item.reset_index(names='Date', inplace=True)
        item['Day'] = item['Date'].dt.day
        item['Month'] = item['Date'].dt.month
        item['Month Name'] = pd.to_datetime(item['Month'], format='%m').dt.strftime('%B')
        item['Year'] = item['Date'].dt.year
        arr.append(item)
    return arr

def monthly_positive_return_stock_list():
    positive_ret_stocks = []
    
    months = list(month_name[1:])
    years = [j for j in range(start_date.year, end_date.year + 1)]
    
    try:    
        for year in years:
            for month in months:
                print(f'Return for {month}-{year}:')
                print()
                for name, df in zip(n50_list, stock_arr):
                    fst_val = df[(df['Year']==year) & (df['Month Name']==month)].head(1)['Adj Close'].values[0]
                    lst_val = df[(df['Year']==year) & (df['Month Name']==month)].tail(1)['Adj Close'].values[0]
                    month_return = lst_val/fst_val - 1

                    if month_return > 0:
                        positive_ret_stocks.append(name)
                        print(f'Return for {name}: {month_return}')
                print()
                print(positive_ret_stocks)
                positive_ret_stocks.clear()
                print('-'*80)
                print()
                
    except:
        return f'wait for next month to complete'

CAGR% (Compound Annual Growth Rate%)¶

In [32]:
def CAGR():
    company_list = []
    cagr_list = []

    
    for item, value in n50_dataframe_list:

            df = value.stock_info_df
            time_min, time_max = df.index.min(), df.index.max()
            time_diff = time_max - time_min
            time_period = time_diff.days/365

            Vbegin = df[df.index == df.index.min()]['Adj Close'][0]
            Vfinal = df[df.index == df.index.max()]['Adj Close'][0]
            
            if time_period == 0:
                time_period = 1
                cagr = ((Vfinal/Vbegin)**(1/time_period) - 1) * 100

                company_list.append(item)
                cagr_list.append(cagr)
            else:
                cagr = ((Vfinal/Vbegin)**(1/time_period) - 1) * 100

                company_list.append(item)
                cagr_list.append(cagr)
                

    cagr_df = pd.DataFrame({'Stock': company_list,
                                 'CAGR%': cagr_list})
    return cagr_df

Volatility %¶

In [34]:
def volatility():
    company_list = []
    volatility_list = []
    
    for item, value in n50_dataframe_list:

        df = value.stock_info_df
        df['Daily Return'] = df['Adj Close'].pct_change().fillna(0)  
        
        daily_ret_std = df['Daily Return'].std()
        vol = np.sqrt(252) * daily_ret_std * 100
        
        company_list.append(item)
        volatility_list.append(vol)
        
    volatility_df = pd.DataFrame({'Stock': company_list,
                                  'Volatility%': volatility_list})
    return volatility_df

Sharpe Ratio¶

In [36]:
def sharpe_ratio():
    company_list = []
    sharpe_ratio_list = []
    
    for item, value in n50_dataframe_list:

        df = value.stock_info_df
        df['Daily Return'] = df['Adj Close'].pct_change().fillna(0)  
        
        daily_ret_std = df['Daily Return'].std()
        daily_ret_mean = df['Daily Return'].mean()
        
        sh_ratio = np.sqrt(252) * (daily_ret_mean / daily_ret_std)
        
        company_list.append(item)
        sharpe_ratio_list.append(sh_ratio)
        
    sharpe_ratio_df = pd.DataFrame({'Stock': company_list,
                                  'Sharpe Ratio': sharpe_ratio_list})
    return sharpe_ratio_df

Max Drawdown (%)¶

In [38]:
def max_DD():
    company_list = []
    max_dd_list = []
    
    for item, value in n50_dataframe_list:

        df = value.stock_info_df
        
        df['Cumulative Return'] = (1 + df['Adj Close'].pct_change()).cumprod() 
        peaks = df['Cumulative Return'].expanding(min_periods=1).max()
        
        drawdowns = df['Cumulative Return'] - peaks
        
        dd_max = drawdowns.min() * 100
        
       
        
        company_list.append(item)
        max_dd_list.append(dd_max)
        
    max_DD_df = pd.DataFrame({'Stock': company_list,
                                  'Max DD (%)': max_dd_list})
    return max_DD_df
